da_jason_hill_climb_nationals_2023-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/emonda_jason_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/emonda_jason_hill_climb_nationals_2023-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/emonda_jason_hill_climb_nationals_2023-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/emonda_jason_hill_climb_nationals_2023-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Charlotte Head</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A cracked Holder just moments after his ride. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Jason Holder’s Trek Émonda spec</h2>\n\n\n\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Frameset</td><td>Trek Émonda</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Weight</td><td>5.3kg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Wheels</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace C24 tubular</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Tyres</td><td>Vittoria Corsa Evo CX tubulars 22mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Groupset</td><td>SRAM Red mechanical</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Brakes</td><td>Bontrager Speed Stop rim brakes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Saddle/seatpost</td><td>Unbranded carbon saddle and seatpost, bonded together</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Crankset</td><td>SRAM Red, Quarq powermeter, AbsoluteBlack chainring</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Cockpit</td><td>Extralite stem, carbon bars</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/trek-emonda-drillium-hill-climb-championship-2023\">‘The saddle’s failed three times so far’: Weight-weenie Trek Émonda’s bonded seatpost and drillium brake pads</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Charlotte Head &#124; Tech Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"32b9bfe2ec6367895d73b3b2bed33f576669bb3130a2ddd3f221397fb34944da","category":"Cycling"}